Post-Install Steps for Property & Casualty OmniStudio

Before exploring the Property & Casualty Application org, you need to complete a few configuration tasks.

Configure the Self-Service Portal: Update any member sites and enable them for standard external profiles so that policyholders and agents can access them.

Configure Sharing Rules for Site Users: Make automatic exceptions to your org-wide sharing settings.

Deactivate and Activate OmniScripts: Deactivate and activate OmniScripts so they can run as intended.

Configure Renewal Notifications: Send email notifications for policies up for renewal by selecting the organization-wide email address in the From field.

Set Up Google Map API Key (optional): Use Google Map APIs to populate address fields, making sure it's enabled for all OmniScripts.

Activate Components: Activate required OmniScripts, FlexCards, flows, and batch jobs for enrollment, termination, and quoting processes.
title: Post-Install Steps for Property & Casualty OmniStudio
